==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|croke|lang=enm}}, {{term|crok|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} *{{term||crōc|hook, bend, crook|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|krōkaz|bend, hook|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|greg-|tracery, basket, bend|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|kreuk||a bend, fold, wrinkle|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|kroke|lang=gml}}, {{term|krake||fold, wrinkle|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|krog||crook, hook|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|krok||crook, hook|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|krókur||hook|lang=is}}.

===Pronunciation===
